# b.scpp itself needs `a` resolvable to be parsed/checked at all (its own
# `import a;`); this does not, by itself, make `a` directly usable from
# main.scpp (see main.scpp's own comment) -- ch11 §11.8's non-transitivity
# is about source-level visibility, independent of how this test harness
# happens to locate each module's source.
a=a.scpp
b=b.scpp
